Thika Town MP Alice Ng&rsquo;ang&rsquo;a has urged Jubilee Party to use the weekend ODM nominations as a lesson. She said JP should ensure its April 21 primaries are free and fair to avoid fallouts.Ng&rsquo;ang&rsquo;a spoke at Maguguni health centre where she distributed food on Friday. She said party members and candidates have faith that the party will hold fair nominations. This is important to ensure losers support the winners, the woman MP said.Ng&rsquo;ang&rsquo;a said the ODM nominations were marred with irregularities and confusion and failed to observe time, making them end in chaos.&ldquo;Those charged with manning the nominations must strictly observe opening and closing time of polling stations,&rdquo; she said.Ng&rsquo;ang&rsquo;a praised the police for maintaining law and order and ensuring peace prevailed in a situation which would have otherwise become violent.